        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Sep 4. 1879</date>
                    <salute>My dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I am sorry to have caused trouble about the £1–16 by my blunder.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
                    <p>As I said I am not sanguine about the sale of the little book, but success apparently depends largely on chance; and it appears to me fair that if above 1500 copies should be sold that I should receive <formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></formula> profits as on former occasions.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I am bound to look after D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Krause’s<ref target="#foot.f3"/> interest (as well as my own) and unless you feel inclined to agree to my proposal, I should prefer publishing on commission, or taking the proof sheets to Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Macmillan<ref target="#foot.f4"/> to see if they will give me larger profits. Do you offer books published on commission at your sale to the booksellers, which I suppose is an advantage? I omitted to state that I shall have pay M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Dallas for translating, and he has translated a good deal more of Krause’s MS than appears to me worth publishing.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
                    <p>A picture of D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Darwin has been photographed by the Autotype C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>, &amp; there only remains to strike off copies, and to ascertain the price per thousand.<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
